 :tx/rationale "Create task: PERF-2: StatusSnapshot compute-once refactor + index wiring — separate computation from presentation in braid status (INV-INTERFACE-008, ADR-STORE-005, INV-QUERY-025). BACKGROUND: braid status takes 8.5s with release binary at 33k datoms. Two root causes: (1) REDUNDANT COMPUTATION: build_json and build_status_projection both independently call compute_fitness, methodology_gaps, default_boundaries().evaluate_all, derive_actions — every expensive function runs TWICE per status invocation. (2) INDEX BYPASS: bilateral.rs has 7 store.datoms() full scans (O(33,800)) and 0 attribute_datoms() index lookups (O(500-1,600)). trilateral.rs has 3 full scans and 0 index lookups. These are the same waste: recomputing what is already known. APPROACH: (1) Define StatusSnapshot struct holding all pre-computed results: fitness: FitnessScore, coherence: CoherenceReport, methodology_score: MethodologyScore, boundary_evaluations: Vec<BoundaryEvaluation>, methodology_gaps: AdjustedGaps, actions: Vec<Action>, action_projection: ProjectedAction, task_counts: (usize, usize, usize), ready_count: usize, trace_staleness: TraceStaleStatus, session_progress: Option<SessionProgress>, tx_since_harvest: usize, p_t: f64. (2) fn compute_status_snapshot(store, path, hashes) -> StatusSnapshot. Inside this function: (a) Call live_projections ONCE, pass to forward_scan_with_projections and backward_scan_with_projections. (b) Call forward_scan and backward_scan using store.attribute_datoms() for :impl/implements (AEVT index, 1,146 datoms instead of 33,800). (c) Call compute_fitness_with_scans reusing the scan results. (d) Call methodology_gaps ONCE. (e) Call derive_actions ONCE. (f) Call default_boundaries().evaluate_all ONCE (with evaluate using index lookups internally). (g) All other cheap computations (task_counts, trace_staleness, session_progress). (3) Rewrite build_json to take &StatusSnapshot instead of &Store — pure formatter, zero store access. (4) Rewrite build_status_projection to take &StatusSnapshot — pure formatter, zero store access. (5) Rewrite build_terse and build_verbose similarly. (6) In run(): let snapshot = compute_status_snapshot(...); then pass &snapshot to all formatters. INDEX WIRING DETAIL: In bilateral.rs forward_scan (line 1015): replace 'for datom in store.datoms()' filtering for :impl/implements with store.attribute_datoms(&implements_attr). In backward_scan: same pattern for impl entity detection. In live_projections (trilateral.rs): replace full scan with per-namespace-attribute AEVT lookups for :spec/element-type, :exploration/category, :impl/source-file etc. In each case the result is identical — the AEVT index returns the same datoms, just without scanning the other 32,000. ISOMORPHISM PROOF: For any store S: (a) store.attribute_datoms(&attr) returns the same set as store.datoms().filter(|d| d.attribute == attr) (guaranteed by INV-STORE-IDX-002, tested by proptest attribute_index_consistency). (b) StatusSnapshot captures exact values that build_json and build_status_projection independently compute — passing pre-computed values produces same output as inline computation (common subexpression elimination). EXPECTED PERFORMANCE: 8.5s → ~0.8s (10x improvement). Store load 0.7s + one computation pass 0.1s using indexes. ACCEPTANCE: (A) braid status produces BIT-FOR-BIT identical output before and after refactor (capture golden output, diff). (B) braid status --format json produces identical JSON. (C) braid status --verbose produces identical verbose output. (D) braid status time < 2s with release binary at 33k datoms. (E) All existing status tests pass unchanged. (F) bilateral.rs has 0 remaining store.datoms() calls that filter by known attribute (no index bypass). (G) trilateral.rs has 0 remaining store.datoms() calls that filter by known attribute. (H) cargo clippy --all-targets clean. FILE: crates/braid/src/commands/status.rs + crates/braid-kernel/src/bilateral.rs + crates/braid-kernel/src/trilateral.rs. TRACES TO: INV-INTERFACE-008, ADR-STORE-005, INV-QUERY-025."
